    <h1>Deployment Page</h1>

    <p>
        This app officially runs on Render; therefore, these deployment steps reflect that. If you haven't already, make sure you have a Render account and the Render CLI before proceeding.
    </p>

    <h2>Setting Up the App in Render</h2>
    <p>Once on the Render dashboard, follow these steps:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Click on <strong>New</strong> then <strong>Web Service</strong>.</li>
        <li>Connect your GitHub or GitLab repository and select the repository for your app.</li>
        <li>Fill out the necessary details, such as the service name and region.</li>
        <li>Choose your build and runtime settings, then click on <strong>Create Web Service</strong>.</li>
        <li>To add a database, navigate to the <strong>Databases</strong> section and create a new PostgreSQL instance.</li>
        <li>For logging, Render provides built-in logs accessible from the app dashboard.</li>
    </ol>


    <p>This completes most of the setup on the Render website. Now we need to set up Google Authentication.</p>

    <h2>Setting up Google Authentication</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Go to <a href="https://cloud.google.com/" target="_blank">Google Cloud</a> and log in or sign up.</li>
        <li>On the Google Cloud welcome page, click on the dropdown box with the three dots and select <strong>NEW PROJECT</strong>.</li>
        <li>After filling out the project information, go to the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, then in the sidebar, find <strong>APIs & Services</strong> &rarr; <strong>Credentials</strong> &rarr; <strong>Configure Consent Screen</strong>.</li>
        <li>Set the User Type to External, then enter the <strong>Application Name, User Support email, and Developer contact information</strong>. Save and continue.</li>
        <li>Return to <strong>Credentials</strong>, click on <strong>Create Credentials</strong>, and select <strong>OAuth Client ID</strong>.</li>
        <li>Select <strong>Web Application</strong>, enter a <strong>Name</strong>, and under <strong>Authorized redirect URIs</strong>, enter: <br>
            <code>https://&lt;renderAppName&gt;.renderapp.com/student_logins/auth/google_oauth2/callback</code>.<br> Click on <strong>Create</strong>.
        </li>
        <li>You will now see the Client ID and Secret. If not, click on the app name in Credentials to retrieve them again. These will link Google Authentication to the Render app.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Linking Google Authentication to the Render App</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>In your terminal, where you downloaded the Render CLI, type <code>render login</code>. Follow the prompt to log in.</li>
        <li>Then, set up the Google Client ID and Secret by running the following commands:
            <pre>
              render config:set GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=&lt;your-client-id&gt;
              render config:set GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=&lt;your-client-secret&gt;
        </pre>
        </li>
    </ol>
